The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Probe into Huma death
                                                                                                                                   Probe into Huma death
                      
	Karachi: Pakistan Prime Minister Yousaf Raza Gilani has asked health officials to probe into the death of former cricket captain Wasim Akrams wife Huma, who expired last month in a Chennai hospital due to multiple organ failure.         
	Federal sports minister Aftab Shah Jillani had visited Akrams residence to offer condolences and was told that his wifes death was a result of doctors negligence.         
	Wasim had demanded that the federal health officials investigate into the treatment provided to his wife in Lahore, one government official said. (PTI)                                                                                                                       
